deck: Finding the demon Azazel in her late parents house, she came under their influence and started killing people.
description:
Origin

Growing up in Sulphur, Oklahoma, Teena became a teacher. After her parents had died, she came back to her parental house to clean it out. There, she found a bottle filled with the demon Azazel. Azazel talked to her and later drove her to kill her best friends.

When Medjine Parker and her siblings stood in front of her door to collect money for the church, Teena invited them in for lemonade. Under the influence of Azazel, Teena started to threaten them and killed one of them. Medjine stood up to her, long enough for the police to arrive. Teena slit her own throat to avoid arrest.

deck: Princess of Atlantis in 50,000 BC.
description:
History

In the year 50,000 BC, Princess Eve was the ruler of Atlantis. During her reign, she was dethroned by her uncle who appointed himself in her place. Under the leadership of the false king Eve was compelled to leave her kingdom behind. During her travels she came upon the Mists of Sleep which like the name suggests made her fall into a deep sleep. It was during this sleep that she was captured by the Witches of Endor who imprisoned her.

While imprisoned Eve was brought out into the open of the stone structure that she was confined to where she was to have a liquid concoction poured on her face in order to burn her which would make her like the other witches. It was at this moment when two other prisoners by the names of Tuk and Tanir rushed to her aid, the two men were able to free Princess Eve. Eve explained her situation to the men with seconds to spare as a crowd of oncoming Witches were on the way to them. The group was able to fight them off leaving them stunned for a time, allowing the three to gather up a few vapor masks to protect themselves from the Mists of Sleep. The three then made it out of the forest and to the outskirts of the Princess's city of Atlantis.

The group at first attempted to enter the city's gates but the false king's sooth-sayer was able to foresee their coming so the king ordered the gates shut. Princess Eve then alerted the group to a secret tunnel that would lead into the city from the hills. She had used the tunnel prior to escape the city in the first place. The tunnel lead into the castle itself where Tuk made short work of the false king but not before he was able to call upon the city's guard. Tanir tussled with the guards for a while before Eve announced her presence to the guards as their Queen. The guards welcomed her return and brought her wicked uncle to the dungeons. Princess Eve offered to repay her new friends but Tanir and Tuk instead decided to continue their journey onward to Attilan, island of the gods.

deck: A very, shy teenager that attends highschool. Also known as Umaru's best friend.
description:
Background

Ebina was originally born in Akita, but at the age of 15 she moved to Tokyo. She lives alone in the Yoshida Apartments, where Umaru and Taihei are residents as well.

Personality

Ebina is known to be very shy. Whenever she is shy or agitated, she reverts her way of speaking to her accent. Occasionally, whenever she receives a compliment she gets distracted. One of the compliments would be directed at her large busts, leading her to be self-consciousness and lost of self-confidence. But at times, she can be very cheerful.
name: Nana Ebina

deck: The older brother of Umaru.
description:
Taihei appears to be fairly slim man, although lacks to have a muscled body. He appears to have ragged, smooth hair with a strand of hair pointed upwards. He has a light skin tone, with brown eyes.

He is often portrayed wearing his work uniform on a constant basis, but at times wears different sets of clothes.

Personality

Taihei is a generous person, who has shown passion for cooking and known to be a pushover to people who slack off. At times, he appears to be a butler, as his sister forces him into cleaning, cooking, and buying whatever she likes. Taihei has also shown to care deeply for his sister, and worries how she will turn out to be as he spoils her.

In certain scenerios, Taihei has appeared to be privately anger towards Umaru, he calms himself down and tries different gestures of kindness in winning her happiness back.

He appears to have a defect, due to showing himself having trouble in remembering his past. Umaru seems to be his only connection.
name: Taihei Doma

deck: Mysterious alien posing as the Hamilton County local newspaper editor. Appears to have the ability to take on human forms. Is wanted on several planets for his war crimes.
description:
Biography

Kroog is a female alien that is wanted for many crimes. Kroog's human form first debuted in Superman #7 unnamed and ordinary. She took the form of a newspaper editor called Candice who was Lois Lane's friend. Kroog was exposed in Superman #12 by Frankenstein. It was revealed that she was wanted by S.H.A.D.E and had a bounty on her head for committing crimes on numerous other planets. Lady Frankenstein also showed up to collect the bounty on Kroog's head. In Superman #13 Kroog evaded capture by blowing herself up and reforming in her spaceship. However, Superman showed up in time to stop her. He used his heat vision to trap her in her space ship. Lady Frankenstein then transported her away to collect her bounty. Her whereabouts are now unknown.
name: Kroog
